[0m$ [0mgit notes add -m "Track: ws-reliability-fixes_20260425

Fixed 6 critical security and reliability issues in WebSocket hub and agent executor:

1. RACE-01 (AgentStateMap thread safety):
   - Added sync.RWMutex to AgentStateMap struct
   - Get() uses RLock/RUnlock for concurrent reads
   - Set()/Clear() use Lock/Unlock for exclusive writes
   - Test: TestAgentStateMap_ConcurrentAccess passes with -race flag

2. LEAK-01 (LogStreamHandler goroutine leak):
   - Replaced <-make(chan struct{}) blocking pattern
   - Added conn.Read goroutine to detect client disconnect
   - defer handles Unsubscribe and Close cleanup

3. LEAK-02 (Hub broadcast FD leak):
   - Added conn.Close() before delete(h.clients, conn)
   - In both subscription path and broadcast path
   - Prevents file descriptor leaks on connection errors

4. SAFE-01 (Binary path validation):
   - Added isValidBinary() whitelist for opencode/gemini/codex
   - Uses filepath.Base() to handle full paths like /usr/bin/opencode
   - Returns error state if binary not in whitelist

5. SAFE-02 (Nil ProcessState dereference):
   - Check cmd.ProcessState != nil before ExitCode() call
   - Only broadcast exit message if ProcessState available

6. LEAK-03 (Hub.Stop() channel closure spin):
   - Added done channel to Hub struct
   - Stop() closes done, run() checks <-h.done first in select
   - Prevents run() from spinning on zero values from closed channels

Files modified:
- internal/agents/types.go (mutex added)
- internal/agents/state_test.go (concurrent test added)
- internal/api/agent_handlers.go (binary validation)
- internal/ws/hub.go (conn.Close, done channel)
- internal/ws/log_stream_handler.go (goroutine fix)
- internal/ws/agent_executor.go (nil check)" 2f32004e92142281354208c7f38bea96040e235c
